message.content:
Analysis of Main Target Image
────────────────────────────

There are two separate “mini‐structures” in the scene:

1) A “chair‐like” figure (left side):
   • Total of 6 blocks arranged in 5 vertical layers.  
   • Bottom layer: two upright green pillars side‐by‐side.  
   • Second layer: a long yellow rectangular prism laid horizontally across the tops of the two green blocks (the “seat”).  
   • Third layer: a red cube resting on the rear portion of the seat.  
   • Fourth layer: a blue cube stacked on top of the red cube.  
   • Fifth (top) layer: a yellow half‐cylinder sitting on the blue cube, oriented so the curved side is “up.”

2) A “car‐like” figure (right side):
   • Total of 5 blocks arranged in 4 layers.  
   • Bottom layer: two red cylinders placed horizontally, side‐by‐side like wheels.  
   • Second layer: a short yellow rectangular prism bridging across and resting on the two cylinders (the “chassis”).  
   • Third layer: a blue cube resting on the rear portion of that yellow block.  
   • Fourth (top) layer: a yellow half‐cylinder resting on the front portion of the same yellow block, again with its curved side “up.”


Dictionary Blocks Required
─────────────────────────

• Chair (6 blocks):
  1) Green vertical pillar (#4) – used twice (for the two legs).  
  2) Yellow horizontal rectangular prism (#6) – once (the seat).  
  3) Red cube (#3) – once.  
  4) Blue cube (#1) – once.  
  5) Yellow half‐cylinder in the correct “curved‐top” orientation (#12) – once.

• Car (5 blocks):
  1) Red horizontal cylinder (#10) – used twice (the two wheels).  
  2) Yellow horizontal rectangular prism (#6) – once (the chassis).  
  3) Blue cube (#1) – once.  
  4) Yellow half‐cylinder (#12) – once (the hood).


Step‐by‐Step Assembly Instructions
──────────────────────────────────

{
  Step1: Move block with index 4   (first green pillar for chair)
  Step2: Move block with index 4   (second green pillar for chair)
  Step3: Move block with index 6   (yellow seat on top of green pillars)
  Step4: Move block with index 3   (red cube on seat)
  Step5: Move block with index 1   (blue cube on red cube)
  Step6: Move block with index 12  (yellow half‐cylinder on top of blue cube)

  Step7: Move block with index 10  (first red wheel for car)
  Step8: Move block with index 10  (second red wheel for car)
  Step9: Move block with index 6   (yellow chassis across wheels)
  Step10: Move block with index 1  (blue cube on rear of chassis)
  Step11: Move block with index 12 (yellow half‐cylinder on front of chassis)
}
